response.title: Handle non existing values in the output table of a list action
response.body:
Some providers do not respect the contract API in Lexicon, and do not provide an id for each returned record during a list action. This leads the generation of the table, which is the default output for a list action, to fail the process and return nothing. See #283.

This PR corrects that by returning an empty string if a given key do not exists in the records given by a provider.

response.title: Some evolutions for Gandi provider
response.body: Following #171: I replaced the option `--api-protocol` by `--auth-api-protocol`. It allows this option, which drives which Gandi API is used, to be defined by an environment variable (here `LEXICON_GANDI_API_PROTOCOL` because only options formated as `--auth-something` can be handled with environment variables. For retro-compatibility, `--api-protocol` is still read but is invisible, and a warning is displayed to the user, indicating that `--auth-api-protocol` should be used for now on.

response.title: Allow to specify --content several times
response.body:
This PR allows the ```--content``` argument to be specified more than one. When it is, an array of strings is provided to the provider.

As all current providers expect to receive a string from the CLI, client.py denormalizes one-element arrays that are passed from the CLI into plain strings, for backward compatibility.
